==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kent bugle
<hw>Kent" bu"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[Probably
named after a <person>Duke of <etsep>Kent</etsep></person>.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A curved bugle, having six finger keys or stops,
by means of which the performer can play upon every key in the musical
scale; -- called also <altname>keyed bugle</altname>, and <altname>key
bugle</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Moore.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kentle</ent>⟦br⟧
